Lacazette&rsquo;s agent speaking about the new normal in transfer markets: &ldquo;At the moment, all EU clubs are first discussing exchange opportunities. It has always been difficult to get these operations done, but we are in an unreal situation.&rdquo; [via @le_Parisien]<br />
<br />
Lacazette&rsquo;s agent: &ldquo;Some clubs will have a budget to make transfers, but there will be far fewer transactions over &euro;20m or &euro;30m which had become normal [not too long ago]&rdquo;

Wilfried Zaha on Arsenal's interest last summer: &quot;It was nice. Supporting them and having them wanting you at the same time, leaves you thinking: 'this is amazing.  But things never worked out so you just have to move on as quick as possible. I was thinking this may happen.<br />
<br />
But my whole family was watching and it just didn't work out.&rdquo;

